      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's great to hear that the redness and swelling have subsided, but it's essential to finish the full course of antibiotics as prescribed, even if you're feeling better. Stopping the medication too early can lead to incomplete treatment, potentially allowing the infection to persist or even causing antibiotic resistance. However, if you're feeling fine, it's likely the infection has cleared up. To be safe, I recommend you follow the full treatment plan and then consult with your doctor for further guidance.",
