      "content": "You're on the right track, considering your gut microbiome's health. While it's true that stopping antibiotics early can help minimize disruption to the gut microbiome, the benefits of early cessation are more nuanced than a straightforward \"better for your overall health\" case. The American Academy of Dermatology recommends completing the full course of antibiotics, even if symptoms resolve, to ensure the infection is fully cleared. However, your doctor may be willing to discuss alternative antibiotics or dosing options that take this into consideration, so it's worth discussing with them.",
